track_notes: Short hike on the Duncan Ridge Trail.  Summit is adjacent to trail.  There was a small campsite you can park at just west of where I joined the trail.  Duncan Ridge Rd is a bit rough and a high-clearance 4WD vehicle is recommended.

Park at the curve in the road.  There is enough room for two vehicles.  It looks like someone has camped there.  Hike a couple hundred feet to the beginning of this track.  There is no obvious trailhead.  Follow this track for a short bushwhack (approximately 150 feet) until you intersect the Duncan Ridge Trail.  Bear left on the Duncan Ridge Trail until you reach the summit of Buckeye Knob.  There are plenty of trees from which you can suspend a wire antenna or a roll-up J-Pole.  Note: Beware of the plethora of bugs during the summer months.  This summit is best hiked during the cold season, when the bugs are dormant and the foliage is minimal. 73, de N4HNH
